news.title: One lakh got houses under PMAY, 8,000 under CMAY in 100 days: Uttar Pradesh Deputy CM
news.para: Deputy chief minister Keshav Prasad Maurya said that the government gave out houses to one lakh people under the PM Awas Yojna and to over 8,000 people under the CM Awas Yojna.

news.title: Kolhapur: No water or power supply to dilapidated buildings
news.para: Maharashtra State Electricity Distribution Company Limited (MSEDCL) and the water supply department of the KMC has been asked to stop both power and water supply.

news.title: Delhi HC asks authorities to inform procedure for allotting newly built vacant houses for EWS
news.para: ​The court was hearing a suo motu petition, initiated on its own while taking note of the situation that a large number of newly constructed houses were lying vacant due to lack of amenities or in a state of partial completion owing to lack of coordination between the authorities.

news.title: Kerala government sanctions Rs 2.2 crore from KIIFB fund for rehab of 36 families
news.para: The rehabilitation of 36 families will be done at Rs 1.61 crore. The amount will be allotted via Kerala Waterways and Infrastructure Ltd.

news.title: Buyers' perspectives are shifting-How can builders tap into this change?
news.para: Streamlining customer experience is a need of the hour, especially at times when competition is skyrocketing. Today, customer segments have evolved and are made up of multiple micro-segments.

news.title: Panel led by Haryana CM to review 74 vigilance complaints in Gurugram civic body
news.para: The complaint against the private firm managing the C&D waste plant in Basai for allegedly violating the terms of agreement is likely to be taken up. Some of these complaints were filed in 2019.

news.title: Noida authority cancels land allotment for ATS Bouquet over Rs 15 crore dues
news.para: The project has 600 units, located in buildings developed for offices and those housing retail spaces, and almost all of them have been sold. Some allottees have already started operating offices from the premises.

news.title: Noida: Old labour cess bills rile house owners, notices served to 1,500
news.para: The department is issuing the notices based on its 2017-18 GIS survey and subsequent construction worth assessments. It started sending the bills in large numbers recently only, since the new commissioner took charge.

news.title: DTCP tells Pivotal Devaan society's builder to fix infra flaws, apply for extra load
news.para: Around 500 families of the society, who have been facing power cuts since Saturday, have questioned how the builder was given an occupancy certificate from DTCP when the society did not have adequate power infrastructure.

news.title: Bring development bodies under RERA ambit, says Credai NCR
news.para: The confederation feels that inordinate delays in procedural work in most of the projects affect timely completion of the same that eventually goes against developers.

news.title: Greater Noida authority tells Supertech to seek IIT audit of Ecovillage-1
news.para: The road has an under-construction basement below it, which would become the basement for towers F5, F7 and D5 once built, and the basement pillars have been twisted and fractured due to the STP work.

news.title: Karnataka: 'A' khata certificates for over 2.5 lakh 'B' khata properties in two months
news.para: “This is a long-pending demand. Several legal issues have to be discussed before the formal decision. We have decided to start issuing ‘A’ khata certificates in two months,” said urban development minister Byrati Basavaraju.

news.title: NBCC may make Rs 1,500 crore from office space sale in Delhi in FY23
news.para: “Despite the pandemic, we have seen an encouraging response from the companies looking for office space in central Delhi,” said Alok Rastogi, senior executive director at NBCC.

news.title: Delhi LG urges residents to 'honestly' pay property taxes to cover deficit
news.para: "MCD services 94% of Delhi. Past financial mismanagement & non payment of any property tax by 75% residents has made it go in RED," Vinai Kumar Saxena tweeted.

news.title: Housing sales in Jan-Jun at nine-year high in top eight cities: Report
news.para: Knight Frank India highlighted that the residential sector has recorded a 9-year high sales volume in January-June 2022. The previous high was recorded in the first half of 2013, when sales were at 1,85,577 units.
